WEBVTT

00:02:28.968 --> 00:02:31.316
I figured I should tell him
what we were doing.

00:02:31.340 --> 00:02:32.369
(Laughter)

00:02:32.393 --> 00:02:35.855
I was terrified; I really thought
I was going to get an eviction notice,

00:02:35.879 --> 00:02:38.189
which really was
the last thing we needed, right?

00:02:38.213 --> 00:02:40.341
I must have caught him
on a good day, though,

00:02:40.365 --> 00:02:42.381
because when I told him what we were doing

00:02:42.405 --> 00:02:45.289
and how we started our nonprofit
urban beekeeping laboratory,

00:02:45.313 --> 00:02:49.212
he said, "That's great!
Let's get a beehive in the back alley."

00:02:49.236 --> 00:02:50.621
I was shocked.

00:02:50.645 --> 00:02:52.443
I was completely surprised.

00:02:52.467 --> 00:02:54.634
I mean, instead of getting
an eviction notice,

00:02:54.658 --> 00:02:56.342
we got another data point.

00:02:56.366 --> 00:02:58.691
And in the back alley of this image,

00:02:58.715 --> 00:03:01.320
what you see here, this hidden beehive --